1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,590
One of the many problems faced when manipulating data using pandas is

2
00:00:04,590 --> 00:00:09,715
converting nested lists so they each have a value represented in a row or column.

3
00:00:09,715 --> 00:00:14,670
To solve this, we use the explode method provided by pandas.

4
00:00:14,670 --> 00:00:20,400
The explode method will convert a list of values into a row representing each value.

5
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:22,845
For every row that has a list,

6
00:00:22,845 --> 00:00:25,305
the result will be a singular column.

7
00:00:25,305 --> 00:00:30,595
We stacked row values representing all of the list values from every row it transform.

8
00:00:30,595 --> 00:00:35,090
Expanding a list into columns does not use the method we just mentioned,

9
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:39,500
but can be achieved by creating a list of values while defining a new DataFrame,

10
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:43,215
effectively transforming the list into columns.

11
00:00:43,215 --> 00:00:44,750
It is important to mention

12
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:48,425
these two transformations as they solve the same problem differently.

13
00:00:48,425 --> 00:00:50,420
Let's go through the notebook to practice

14
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:54,600
the two techniques and visually understand their distinctions.

